<!-- Node: "Unreal Tournament 2004 Demo Unleashed" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Unreal Tournament 2004 Demo Unleashed</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">G.A.R.D.</a> on Thursday, February 12, 2004 - 06:04</small><br /><br />
Atari and Epic Games have released the <a href="http://www.unrealtournament.com">official demo for Unreal Tournament 2004</a>. Yippy! You can down load the demo from www.unrealtournament.com as well as from several worldwide mirror. <BR> <BR>

<i>" The Unreal Tournament 2004 official demo includes five playable game modes, and offers fans their first taste of Unreal Tournament 2004’s two new game modes: the introduction of the hyper-charged Onslaught mode and the return of the fan-favorite Assault mode, which last appeared in the original Unreal Tournament. The demo also features established gametypes like Deathmatch, Capture the Flag and Bombing Run ... "</i>
